        "name": "Red Cap",
        "subtype": "ability",
        "text": "A redcap's woolen hat is dyed with the blood of their victims. If the redcap loses their cap, they no longer benefit from fast healing and take a \u20134 status penalty to their damage rolls. They can create a new cap in 10 minutes, but that cap doesn't grant them powers until the redcap has turned it red with Blood Soak. A cap has no benefit for creatures other than the redcap who made it.",
        "traits": [
          {
            "alternate_link": {
              "alternate_type": "legacy",
              "aonid": 134,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "type": "alternate_link"
            },
            "edition": "remastered",
            "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "Primal",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "2.0",
                  "aonid": 216,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "2.0",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                  "aonid": 216,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Player Core",
                "page": 460,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
            "type": "trait"
          }
        ],
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    ],
